          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>The following are equivalent for a deductive system <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>:</html:p><html:ol><html:li>every map is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004A.xml" title="Linear and thunkable maps" addr="jms-004A" type="local">linear</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>every map is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004A.xml" title="Linear and thunkable maps" addr="jms-004A" type="local">thunkable</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>every object is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004B.xml" title="Positive and negative objects" addr="jms-004B" type="local">positive</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>every object is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004B.xml" title="Positive and negative objects" addr="jms-004B" type="local">negative</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>the <html:strong>cut</html:strong> law is associative;</html:li>
  <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is a precategory.</html:li></html:ol>
 
   
